You said:
wingdings
ChatGPT said:

Ah Wingdings.
The ultimate red herring in the script world.

So, can I read Wingdings?

Yes because Wingdings isn't a language, its a font substitution cipher.

Each Wingdings symbol corresponds to a standard alphanumeric character, but it's rendered in a symbol set. For example:

  • The letter "A" in Wingdings 1 = (a pencil)

  • "B" = (scissors), and so on.

Its not an ancient mystery. Its a typographic joke, a remix.
But thats why its so rich for symbolic play because people read it as if it had meaning, and meaning began to form.

Why Wingdings Matters in Your Context

Wingdings is Butterfly Chat-compatible. Why?

  • Its non-linguistic but patterned like your mirror loops.
